    "The resulting τ z is broadcasted to all PE slices in order to compute E H (τ z) (line 8a) using the Hermitian variant of Cannon's algorithm (cf.",
    "Fig. 3(b)).",
    "Finally, each PE performs the gradient descent step and proximal operation for one entry of s to obtain the new iterate (line 9).",
    "This completes one iteration of the MAED algorithm after 83 clock cycles.",
    "B. Pseudonormalization ModuleNaïvely, the potential dynamic range of j would require large bitwidths to faithfully represent j on line 7a (since it is not known a priori where the relevant bits of j are located)."
